fields.name: call_id
fields.desc: Call identifier.

fields.name: protocol
fields.desc: Description of the call protocols supported by the application.

acceptCall.desc:
Accepts an incoming call.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: terms_of_service_id
fields.desc: Terms of service identifier.

acceptTermsOfService.desc:
Accepts Telegram terms of services.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: chat_id
fields.desc: Chat identifier.

fields.name: user_ids
fields.desc: Identifiers of the users to be added to the chat.

addChatMembers.desc:
Adds multiple new members to a chat. Currently this option is only available for supergroups and channels. This option can't be used to join a chat. Members can't be added to a channel if it has more than 200 members. Members will not be added until the chat state has been synchronized with the server.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: chat_id
fields.desc: Chat identifier.

fields.name: user_id
fields.desc: Identifier of the user.

fields.name: forward_limit
fields.desc: The number of earlier messages from the chat to be forwarded to the new member; up to 100. Ignored for supergroups and channels.

addChatMember.desc:
Adds a new member to a chat. Members can't be added to private or secret chats. Members will not be added until the chat state has been synchronized with the server.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: language_pack_id
fields.desc: Identifier of a language pack to be added; may be different from a name that is used in an "https://t.me/setlanguage/" link.

addCustomServerLanguagePack.desc:
Adds a custom server language pack to the list of installed language packs in current localization target. Can be called before authorization.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: contact
fields.desc: The contact to add or edit; phone number can be empty and needs to be specified only if known, vCard is ignored.

fields.name: share_phone_number
fields.desc: True, if the new contact needs to be allowed to see current user's phone number. A corresponding rule to userPrivacySettingShowPhoneNumber will be added if needed. Use the field UserFullInfo.need_phone_number_privacy_exception to check whether the current user needs to be asked to share their phone number.

addContact.desc:
Adds a user to the contact list or edits an existing contact by their user identifier.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: sticker
fields.desc: Sticker file to add.

addFavoriteSticker.desc:
Adds a new sticker to the list of favorite stickers. The new sticker is added to the top of the list. If the sticker was already in the list, it is removed from the list first. Only stickers belonging to a sticker set can be added to this list.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: chat_id
fields.desc: Target chat.

fields.name: sender
fields.desc: The sender sender of the message.

fields.name: reply_to_message_id
fields.desc: Identifier of the message to reply to or 0.

fields.name: disable_notification
fields.desc: Pass true to disable notification for the message.

fields.name: input_message_content
fields.desc: The content of the message to be added.

addLocalMessage.desc:
Adds a local message to a chat. The message is persistent across application restarts only if the message database is used. Returns the added message.
Returns object_ptr<Message>.

fields.name: chat_id
fields.desc: Chat identifier.

fields.name: chat_list
fields.desc: The chat list. Use getChatListsToAddChat to get suitable chat lists.

addChatToList.desc:
Adds a chat to a chat list. A chat can't be simultaneously in Main and Archive chat lists, so it is automatically removed from another one if needed.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: verbosity_level
fields.desc: The minimum verbosity level needed for the message to be logged, 0-1023.

fields.name: text
fields.desc: Text of a message to log.

addLogMessage.desc:
Adds a message to TDLib internal log. Can be called synchronously.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: entry
fields.desc: The network statistics entry with the data to be added to statistics.

addNetworkStatistics.desc:
Adds the specified data to data usage statistics. Can be called before authorization.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: server
fields.desc: Proxy server IP address.

fields.name: port
fields.desc: Proxy server port.

fields.name: enable
fields.desc: True, if the proxy should be enabled.

fields.name: type
fields.desc: Proxy type.

addProxy.desc:
Adds a proxy server for network requests. Can be called before authorization.
Returns object_ptr<Proxy>.

fields.name: is_attached
fields.desc: Pass true to add the sticker to the list of stickers recently attached to photo or video files; pass false to add the sticker to the list of recently sent stickers.

fields.name: sticker
fields.desc: Sticker file to add.

addRecentSticker.desc:
Manually adds a new sticker to the list of recently used stickers. The new sticker is added to the top of the list. If the sticker was already in the list, it is removed from the list first. Only stickers belonging to a sticker set can be added to this list.
Returns object_ptr<Stickers>.

fields.name: chat_id
fields.desc: Identifier of the chat to add.

addRecentlyFoundChat.desc:
Adds a chat to the list of recently found chats. The chat is added to the beginning of the list. If the chat is already in the list, it will be removed from the list first.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: user_id
fields.desc: Sticker set owner.

fields.name: name
fields.desc: Sticker set name.

fields.name: sticker
fields.desc: Sticker to add to the set.

addStickerToSet.desc:
Adds a new sticker to a set; for bots only. Returns the sticker set.
Returns object_ptr<StickerSet>.

fields.name: animation
fields.desc: The animation file to be added. Only animations known to the server (i.e. successfully sent via a message) can be added to the list.

addSavedAnimation.desc:
Manually adds a new animation to the list of saved animations. The new animation is added to the beginning of the list. If the animation was already in the list, it is removed first. Only non-secret video animations with MIME type "video/mp4" can be added to the list.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: custom_query_id
fields.desc: Identifier of a custom query.

fields.name: data
fields.desc: JSON-serialized answer to the query.

answerCustomQuery.desc:
Answers a custom query; for bots only.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: callback_query_id
fields.desc: Identifier of the callback query.

fields.name: text
fields.desc: Text of the answer.

fields.name: show_alert
fields.desc: If true, an alert should be shown to the user instead of a toast notification.

fields.name: url
fields.desc: URL to be opened.

fields.name: cache_time
fields.desc: Time during which the result of the query can be cached, in seconds.

answerCallbackQuery.desc:

fields.desc: Allowed time to cache the results of the query, in seconds.

fields.desc: Offset for the next inline query; pass an empty string if there are no more results.

fields.desc: If non-empty, this text should be shown on the button that opens a private chat with the bot and sends a start message to the bot with the parameter switch_pm_parameter.

fields.name: switch_pm_parameter
fields.desc: The parameter for the bot start message.

answerInlineQuery.desc:
Sets the result of an inline query; for bots only.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: pre_checkout_query_id
fields.desc: Identifier of the pre-checkout query.

fields.name: error_message
fields.desc: An error message, empty on success.

answerPreCheckoutQuery.desc:
Sets the result of a pre-checkout query; for bots only.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: shipping_query_id
fields.desc: Identifier of the shipping query.

fields.name: shipping_options
fields.desc: Available shipping options.

fields.name: error_message
fields.desc: An error message, empty on success.

answerShippingQuery.desc:
Sets the result of a shipping query; for bots only.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: message_id
fields.desc: The identifier of an incoming message in the Replies chat.

fields.name: delete_message
fields.desc: Pass true if the message must be deleted.

fields.name: delete_all_messages
fields.desc: Pass true if all messages from the same sender must be deleted.

fields.name: report_spam
fields.desc: Pass true if the sender must be reported to the Telegram moderators.

blockMessageSenderFromReplies.desc:
Blocks an original sender of a message in the Replies chat.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

canTransferOwnership.desc:
Checks whether the current session can be used to transfer a chat ownership to another user.
Returns object_ptr<CanTransferOwnershipResult>.

fields.name: file_id
fields.desc: Identifier of a file to stop downloading.

fields.name: only_if_pending
fields.desc: Pass true to stop downloading only if it hasn't been started, i.e. request hasn't been sent to server.

cancelDownloadFile.desc:
Stops the downloading of a file. If a file has already been downloaded, does nothing.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: file_id
fields.desc: Identifier of the file to stop uploading.

cancelUploadFile.desc:
Stops the uploading of a file. Supported only for files uploaded by using uploadFile. For other files the behavior is undefined.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: contacts
fields.desc: The new list of contacts, contact's vCard are ignored and are not imported.

changeImportedContacts.desc:
Changes imported contacts using the list of current user contacts saved on the device. Imports newly added contacts and, if at least the file database is enabled, deletes recently deleted contacts. Query result depends on the result of the previous query, so only one query is possible at the same time.
Returns object_ptr<ImportedContacts>.

fields.name: phone_number
fields.desc: The new phone number of the user in international format.

fields.name: settings
fields.desc: Settings for the authentication of the user's phone number.

changePhoneNumber.desc:
Changes the phone number of the user and sends an authentication code to the user's new phone number. On success, returns information about the sent code.
Returns object_ptr<AuthenticationCodeInfo>.

fields.name: set_id
fields.desc: Identifier of the sticker set.

fields.name: is_installed
fields.desc: The new value of is_installed.

fields.name: is_archived
fields.desc: The new value of is_archived. A sticker set can't be installed and archived simultaneously.

changeStickerSet.desc:
Installs/uninstalls or activates/archives a sticker set.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: token
fields.desc: The bot token.

checkAuthenticationBotToken.desc:
Checks the authentication token of a bot; to log in as a bot. Works only when the current authorization state is authorizationStateWaitPhoneNumber. Can be used instead of setAuthenticationPhoneNumber and checkAuthenticationCode to log in.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: code
fields.desc: The verification code received via SMS, Telegram message, phone call, or flash call.

checkAuthenticationCode.desc:
Checks the authentication code. Works only when the current authorization state is authorizationStateWaitCode.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: password
fields.desc: The password to check.

checkAuthenticationPassword.desc:
Checks the authentication password for correctness. Works only when the current authorization state is authorizationStateWaitPassword.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: code
fields.desc: Verification code received by SMS, phone call or flash call.

checkChangePhoneNumberCode.desc:
Checks the authentication code sent to confirm a new phone number of the user.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: invite_link
fields.desc: Invite link to be checked; should begin with "https://t.me/joinchat/", "https://telegram.me/joinchat/", or "https://telegram.dog/joinchat/".

checkChatInviteLink.desc:
Checks the validity of an invite link for a chat and returns information about the corresponding chat.
Returns object_ptr<ChatInviteLinkInfo>.

fields.name: type
fields.desc: Type of the public chats, for which to check the limit.

checkCreatedPublicChatsLimit.desc:
Checks whether the maximum number of owned public chats has been reached. Returns corresponding error if the limit was reached.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: encryption_key
fields.desc: Encryption key to check or set up.

checkDatabaseEncryptionKey.desc:
Checks the database encryption key for correctness. Works only when the current authorization state is authorizationStateWaitEncryptionKey.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: chat_id
fields.desc: Chat identifier; should be identifier of a supergroup chat, or a channel chat, or a private chat with self, or zero if chat is being created.

fields.name: username
fields.desc: Username to be checked.

checkChatUsername.desc:
Checks whether a username can be set for a chat.
Returns object_ptr<CheckChatUsernameResult>.

fields.name: code
fields.desc: Verification code.

checkEmailAddressVerificationCode.desc:
Checks the email address verification code for Telegram Passport.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: code
fields.desc: The phone number confirmation code.

checkPhoneNumberConfirmationCode.desc:
Checks phone number confirmation code.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: code
fields.desc: Verification code.

checkPhoneNumberVerificationCode.desc:
Checks the phone number verification code for Telegram Passport.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: code
fields.desc: Verification code.

checkRecoveryEmailAddressCode.desc:
Checks the 2-step verification recovery email address verification code.
Returns object_ptr<PasswordState>.

fields.name: file_name
fields.desc: File name or path to the file.

cleanFileName.desc:
Removes potentially dangerous characters from the name of a file. The encoding of the file name is supposed to be UTF-8. Returns an empty string on failure. Can be called synchronously.
Returns object_ptr<Text>.

clearImportedContacts.desc:
Clears all imported contacts, contact list remains unchanged.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: exclude_secret_chats
fields.desc: If true, local draft messages in secret chats will not be cleared.

clearAllDraftMessages.desc:
Clears draft messages in all chats.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: is_attached
fields.desc: Pass true to clear the list of stickers recently attached to photo or video files; pass false to clear the list of recently sent stickers.

clearRecentStickers.desc:
Clears the list of recently used stickers.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

close.desc:
Closes the TDLib instance. All databases will be flushed to disk and properly closed. After the close completes, updateAuthorizationState with authorizationStateClosed will be sent. Can be called before initialization.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

clearRecentlyFoundChats.desc:
Clears the list of recently found chats.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: chat_id
fields.desc: Chat identifier.

closeChat.desc:
Informs TDLib that the chat is closed by the user. Many useful activities depend on the chat being opened or closed.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: secret_chat_id
fields.desc: Secret chat identifier.

closeSecretChat.desc:
Closes a secret chat, effectively transferring its state to secretChatStateClosed.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: link
fields.desc: A link from a QR code. The link must be scanned by the in-app camera.

confirmQrCodeAuthentication.desc:
Confirms QR code authentication on another device. Returns created session on success.
Returns object_ptr<Session>.

fields.name: basic_group_id
fields.desc: Basic group identifier.

fields.name: force
fields.desc: If true, the chat will be created without network request. In this case all information about the chat except its type, title and photo can be incorrect.

createBasicGroupChat.desc:
Returns an existing chat corresponding to a known basic group.
Returns object_ptr<Chat>.

fields.name: user_id
fields.desc: Identifier of the user to be called.

fields.name: protocol
fields.desc: Description of the call protocols supported by the application.

fields.name: is_video
fields.desc: True, if a video call needs to be created.

createCall.desc:
Creates a new call.
Returns object_ptr<CallId>.

fields.name: filter

createChatFilter.desc:
Creates new chat filter. Returns information about the created chat filter.
Returns object_ptr<ChatFilterInfo>.

fields.name: user_ids
fields.desc: Identifiers of users to be added to the basic group.

fields.name: title
fields.desc: Title of the new basic group; 1-128 characters.

createNewBasicGroupChat.desc:
Creates a new basic group and sends a corresponding messageBasicGroupChatCreate. Returns the newly created chat.
Returns object_ptr<Chat>.

fields.name: user_id
fields.desc: Identifier of the target user.

createNewSecretChat.desc:
Creates a new secret chat. Returns the newly created chat.
Returns object_ptr<Chat>.

fields.desc: Sticker set owner.

fields.name: title
fields.desc: Sticker set title; 1-64 characters.

fields.name: name
fields.desc: Sticker set name. Can contain only English letters, digits and underscores. Must end with "by" ( is case insensitive); 1-64 characters.

fields.name: is_masks
fields.desc: True, if stickers are masks. Animated stickers can't be masks.

fields.name: stickers
fields.desc: List of stickers to be added to the set; must be non-empty. All stickers must be of the same type.

createNewStickerSet.desc:
Creates a new sticker set; for bots only. Returns the newly created sticker set.
Returns object_ptr<StickerSet>.

fields.name: title
fields.desc: Title of the new chat; 1-128 characters.

fields.name: is_channel
fields.desc: True, if a channel chat should be created.

fields.name: description
fields.desc: Chat description; 0-255 characters.

fields.name: location
fields.desc: Chat location if a location-based supergroup is being created.

createNewSupergroupChat.desc:
Creates a new supergroup or channel and sends a corresponding messageSupergroupChatCreate. Returns the newly created chat.
Returns object_ptr<Chat>.

fields.name: user_id
fields.desc: User identifier.

fields.name: force
fields.desc: If true, the chat will be created without network request. In this case all information about the chat except its type, title and photo can be incorrect.

createPrivateChat.desc:
Returns an existing chat corresponding to a given user.
Returns object_ptr<Chat>.

fields.name: supergroup_id
fields.desc: Supergroup or channel identifier.

fields.name: force
fields.desc: If true, the chat will be created without network request. In this case all information about the chat except its type, title and photo can be incorrect.

createSupergroupChat.desc:
Returns an existing chat corresponding to a known supergroup or channel.
Returns object_ptr<Chat>.

fields.name: secret_chat_id
fields.desc: Secret chat identifier.

createSecretChat.desc:
Returns an existing chat corresponding to a known secret chat.
Returns object_ptr<Chat>.

fields.name: reason
fields.desc: The reason why the account was deleted; optional.

deleteAccount.desc:
Deletes the account of the current user, deleting all information associated with the user from the server. The phone number of the account can be used to create a new account. Can be called before authorization when the current authorization state is authorizationStateWaitPassword.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: password
fields.desc: Persistent user password.

fields.name: valid_for
fields.desc: Time during which the temporary password will be valid, in seconds; should be between 60 and 86400.

createTemporaryPassword.desc:
Creates a new temporary password for processing payments.
Returns object_ptr<TemporaryPasswordState>.

fields.name: chat_filter_id
fields.desc: Chat filter identifier.

deleteChatFilter.desc:
Deletes existing chat filter.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: chat_id
fields.desc: Chat identifier.

fields.name: remove_from_chat_list
fields.desc: Pass true if the chat should be removed from the chat list.

fields.name: revoke
fields.desc: Pass true to try to delete chat history for all users.

deleteChatHistory.desc:
Deletes all messages in the chat. Use Chat.can_be_deleted_only_for_self and Chat.can_be_deleted_for_all_users fields to find whether and how the method can be applied to the chat.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: chat_id
fields.desc: Chat identifier.

fields.name: user_id
fields.desc: User identifier.

deleteChatMessagesFromUser.desc:
Deletes all messages sent by the specified user to a chat. Supported only for supergroups; requires can_delete_messages administrator privileges.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: chat_id
fields.desc: Chat identifier.

fields.name: message_id
fields.desc: The message identifier of the used keyboard.

deleteChatReplyMarkup.desc:
Deletes the default reply markup from a chat. Must be called after a one-time keyboard or a ForceReply reply markup has been used. UpdateChatReplyMarkup will be sent if the reply markup will be changed.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: file_id
fields.desc: Identifier of the file to delete.

deleteFile.desc:
Deletes a file from the TDLib file cache.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.desc: Chat identifier.

fields.name: message_ids
fields.desc: Identifiers of the messages to be deleted.

fields.name: revoke
fields.desc: Pass true to try to delete messages for all chat members. Always true for supergroups, channels and secret chats.

fields.name: language_pack_id
fields.desc: Identifier of the language pack to delete.

deleteLanguagePack.desc:
Deletes all information about a language pack in the current localization target. The language pack which is currently in use (including base language pack) or is being synchronized can't be deleted. Can be called before authorization.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: type
fields.desc: Element type.

deletePassportElement.desc:
Deletes a Telegram Passport element.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: profile_photo_id
fields.desc: Identifier of the profile photo to delete.

deleteProfilePhoto.desc:
Deletes a profile photo.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

deleteSavedCredentials.desc:
Deletes saved credentials for all payment provider bots.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

deleteSavedOrderInfo.desc:
Deletes saved order info.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.name: supergroup_id
fields.desc: Identifier of the supergroup or channel.

deleteSupergroup.desc:
Deletes a supergroup or channel along with all messages in the corresponding chat. This will release the supergroup or channel username and remove all members; requires owner privileges in the supergroup or channel. Chats with more than 1000 members can't be deleted using this method.

Closes the TDLib instance, destroying all local data without a proper logout. The current user session will remain in the list of all active sessions. All local data will be destroyed. Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

disableProxy.desc:
Disables the currently enabled proxy. Can be called before authorization.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

disconnectAllWebsites.desc:
Disconnects all websites from the current user's Telegram account.

disconnectWebsite.desc:
Disconnects website from the current user's Telegram account.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.desc: The starting position from which the file should be downloaded.

fields.desc: Number of bytes which should be downloaded starting from the "offset" position before the download will be automatically cancelled; use 0 to download without a limit.

fields.desc: If false, this request returns file state just after the download has been started. If true, this request returns file state only after the download has succeeded, has failed, has been cancelled or a new downloadFile request with different offset/limit parameters was sent.

downloadFile.desc:
Downloads a file from the cloud. Download progress and completion of the download will be notified through updateFile updates.
Returns object_ptr<File>.

fields.name: info

editCustomLanguagePackInfo.desc:

Uniquely identifies a file, but a file can have a lot of different valid identifiers. If the ID starts with "http://" or "https://", it represents the HTTP URL of the file. TDLib is currently unable to download files if only their URL is known. If downloadFile is called on such a file or if it is sent to a secret chat, TDLib starts a file generation process by sending updateFileGenerationStart to the application with the HTTP URL in the original_path and "#url#" as the conversion string. Application should generate the file by downloading it to the specified location.
